### Deploy example function
POST http://localhost:5000/deploy/example HTTP/1.1


### Check deployment status (paste id from deploy response)
GET http://localhost:5000/deploy/status/{{deployment_id}} HTTP/1.1


### List tracked replicas in Redis
GET http://localhost:5000/functions/example/replicas HTTP/1.1


### Invoke example #1
POST http://localhost:5000/invoke/example HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{
	"name": "test-1"
}


### Invoke example #2
POST http://localhost:5000/invoke/example HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{
	"name": "test-2"
}


### Invoke example #3
POST http://localhost:5000/invoke/example HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{
	"name": "test-3"
}


### Deploy rust analytics function
POST http://localhost:5000/deploy/example-rust HTTP/1.1


### Invoke rust analytics function
POST http://localhost:5000/invoke/example-rust HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{
	"jobId": "energy-window-2026-04-05-08",
	"facilityId": "factory-north-1",
	"meterId": "line-a-main-meter",
	"windowStart": "2026-04-05T08:00:00Z",
	"pricePerKwhUsd": 0.17,
	"readings": [
		{ "timestamp": "2026-04-05T08:00:00Z", "watts": 12850.0 },
		{ "timestamp": "2026-04-05T08:01:00Z", "watts": 13120.0 },
		{ "timestamp": "2026-04-05T08:02:00Z", "watts": 12960.0 },
		{ "timestamp": "2026-04-05T08:03:00Z", "watts": 18840.0 },
		{ "timestamp": "2026-04-05T08:04:00Z", "watts": 13040.0 },
		{ "timestamp": "2026-04-05T08:05:00Z", "watts": 12790.0 }
	],
	"rounds": 900
}


### Update example-rust config
PATCH http://localhost:5000/functions/example-rust HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{
	"memory": 512,
	"replicas": 4,
	"loadBalancer": "weighted_priority",
	"replicaWeights": [3, 1, 1, 1]
}


### Stop function and remove its containers
POST http://localhost:5000/functions/example-rust/stop HTTP/1.1


### Show all deployed functions
GET http://localhost:5000/functions HTTP/1.1
